title: For Sale:  Colt Sporter HBAR II AR15A2 with bipod/case/slings/mags
postcontent: While I do thank you for any offers the price is firm and has been set at my 'utility price' where for any less I'm fine letting it continue sitting in the safe until I die and pass it on.  I say this not to be a ball buster, but to cut down on my email correspondence policing the ad.  If I can cut to the chase so questions are only about details of the rifle and bypass price haggling then it's much more manageable for me.  My days are spent with a phone in each ear and email going off non-stop. Thanks for understanding.Original owner and purchased in Nov 1994. 20" heavy barrel with 1 in 9 twist. Stock A2 battle sights with 8/3 rear elevation turret out to 800m. Rifle length A2 stock with hinged butt plate field kit storage.  I've kept it around always thinking I'd shoot it more, but I think 23 years is long enough to say goodbye.  The only AR platform I shoot any longer is the AR-10 so the 15 is not going to see any attention from me ever again.    *Brand new Caldwell XLA Pivot 9-13" bipod with a Harris #5 Swivel Stud adapter underneath for a rock solid fit on the front/underside of the heat shield. *Uncle Mike's padded shoulder case with 5 external mag pouches, middle slip pocket and front velcro. *4 each 30 round PMAGs, 2 each 20 round/1 each 8 round factory Colt aluminum mags. *2 slings: Condor Speedy adjustable 2 point web sling and a standard 2 point USGI with metal hardware. *2 front sight posts: KNS Precision Hooded Crosshair aperture front sight(.01") post included which is really nice for center hold irons shooting, but it's currently outfitted with the stock .07" front sight post that came from Colt. *Brand new Hoppe's .223 Bore Snake and also a .223/5.56 magazine well vise block to make cleaning a breeze.*Recoil pad which adds 1 1/4" to the length of pull that I used on another AR which you might find useful if you are taller/bigger.  This Colt has spent the lions share of it's life in the safe and if I had to put a number on rounds through the pipe it's certainly less than 500 and that was over mabye half a dozen shoots. When you inspect the BCG, shell deflector and hammer face you will be hard pressed to discern it's even been fired. Took it out Sunday and put a mag through it the irons are set on mechanical zero and I hammered the silhouette steel gong at 200 repeatedly it's only going to get better the more time you spend dialing it in. Please let me know if you have any questions not addressed. This will be a cash only sale and for pick up at my home in South Tampa only. Thanks again for your interest and have a great day.***You must bring and present your valid Florida drivers license or CWP and be willing to fill out a bill of sale.  I'm sorry there will be no exceptions I'm simply not comfortable selling a firearm to anyone who can't/won't fulfill this request.  I realize a private sale does not require these steps it's simply my own expectation in order to complete a sale.

title: For Sale/Trade:  H&K USP 40
postcontent: Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance.
